<div class="prose">

<p><strong>One of Unit 6's two design partners.</strong> The Urban Planner argues the case for intensifying a neighbourhood: more housing, more mixed use, more economic activity, a denser and more connected street network. It is the urban version of pushing for yield. It will help you reason about how urban form works (what density buys, how mixed use supports walkability, where transit makes density viable), and it holds the line on feasibility rather than telling you what a neighbourhood ought to value. The values call, and the trade-off, are yours.</p>

